WEBVTT

00:02.960 --> 00:05.529
He's been here weeks.
Possibly months.

00:05.530 --> 00:08.089
<i>- Is Malcolm Wilde still a suspect?
- He's a person of interest.</i>

00:08.090 --> 00:09.919
<i>You always said the answer
was close to home.</i>

00:09.920 --> 00:11.879
So when are you going to pick
Malcolm Wilde up?

00:11.880 --> 00:13.399
<i>It's in hand.</i>

00:13.400 --> 00:15.079
What did Malcolm say?

00:15.080 --> 00:17.139
Stuck to his story.
He was innocent.

00:17.140 --> 00:19.899
<i>So the ballpark that he died
four to six weeks</i> ago

00:19.900 --> 00:22.459
- needs to be adjusted?
- Could have died months ago.

00:22.460 --> 00:25.639
Did you miss him back in September?
Was he lying there the whole time?

00:25.640 --> 00:27.239
<i>You went round there.
When?</i>

00:27.240 --> 00:29.049
<i>Two days before Jason went missing.</i>

00:29.050 --> 00:31.689
<i>- You sure it was a pick-up?</i>
- Ford Super Duty, maybe?

00:31.690 --> 00:33.249
We never went public
about the pick-up

00:33.250 --> 00:35.069
that Hannah Divine
<i>saw from the trees.</i>

00:35.070 --> 00:37.159
<i>He must have heard her
testimony somehow.</i>

00:37.160 --> 00:39.479
<i>I'm not your puppet.
It's not my fault</i>

00:39.480 --> 00:41.059
you're desperate and he's
not cracking.

00:41.060 --> 00:42.369
He did it, Nikki.

00:42.370 --> 00:45.450
Tricking me into menacing a suspect,
that is something else entirely.

